<subSubSection id="4B3FF5BC8B4B33CB45C7CE96D3080CAF" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="type">
<paragraph id="D3840D9F3E4BDE27D1E323D725273E32" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B11703DC1AF646343BD22F082F483605" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
ITALY, Sicily (lectotype LINN 218.40!, designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="0689DDB01C3331551F4C2807D1FEE4B0" author="Verdcourt, B" editor="Hubbard, CE" journalOrPublisher="HMSO, London" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 161" refId="B373" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1963. Convolvulaceae. In: Hubbard, CE, Milne-Redhead, E, Eds., Flora of Tropical East Africa. HMSO, London: 1 - 161" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Tropical East Africa." year="1963">Verdcourt 1963</bibRefCitation>
: 41).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="84836CB8CBAB61AEFE122B9024FD5ED4" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph id="2E030CC17FAF98F78BF9F3C47C9C0655" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C54B569B654F20BEF3C0E2FABC7FD8F4" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
Annual herb, commonly branched at base with prostrate to erect stems to 40 cm long, thinly pilose with brownish hairs on vegetative parts. Leaves petiolate, 1-5 
<normalizedToken id="82E97BFDF2DAFC25572B2F10134DA0D9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-2 cm, ovate-deltoid, acute, base cuneate to abruptly truncate, margin entire; petioles 2-5 (-11) mm. Flowers 1-3 (-4); peduncles 0.6-2.5 cm, bracteoles 2-11 
<normalizedToken id="418B2DB16959D7DBB9869F17D36E43AE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, filiform, linear or linear-lanceolate; pedicels 0-10 mm, becoming recurved in fruit; outer sepals 5-6 
<normalizedToken id="4594150575545CF10C808956BC478514" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-3 mm, lanceolate, ovate to subrhomboid, acute; corolla 5-7 mm long, white or lilac, deeply lobed for c. 2 mm, midpetaline bands glabrous; filaments glandular below; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided c. 2 mm above base, stigmas 2 mm. Capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous, tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation id="D1D0F937CF29F37D96091CB236251B60" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="18191AEDBA688C46D729339363A06440" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 197; 
<bibRefCitation id="438C099D0FBFF31ADC0E3BD7C41ABCFA" author="Feinbrun-Dothan, N" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" pagination="33 - 43" refId="B119" refString="Feinbrun-Dothan, N, 1978. Flora Palaestina volumen 3: Ericaceae to Compositae. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem: 33 - 43" title="Flora Palaestina volumen 3: Ericaceae to Compositae" year="1978">Feinbrun-Dothan 1978</bibRefCitation>
plate 62); 
<bibRefCitation id="1465E17A7C3DD2A297E030C04D0E5DBB" author="Collenette, S" journalOrPublisher="National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh" pageId="201" pageNumber="202" pagination="1 - 799" refId="B92" refString="Collenette, S, 1999. Wild flowers of Saudi Arabia. National Commission for Wildlife Conservation and Development, Riyadh: 1 - 799" title="Wild flowers of Saudi Arabia" year="1999">Collenette 1999</bibRefCitation>
: 232 (photo); 
<bibRefCitation id="ECA4135A130E7A721438F4995C1ED502" author="Silvestre, S" editor="Talevera, S" journalOrPublisher="Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid" pageId="211" pageNumber="212" pagination="252 - 273" refId="B337" refString="Silvestre, S, 2012. Convolvulus. In: Talevera, S, Andres, C, Arista, M, Fernandes Piedra, MP, Gallego, MJ, Ortiz, PL, Romero Zarco, C, Salgueiro, FJ, Silvestre, S, Quinanar, A, Eds., Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae. Real Jardin Botanico, CSIC, Madrid: 252 - 273" title="Convolvulus." volumeTitle="Flora Iberica volume 11: Gentianaceae to Boraginaceae." year="2012">Silvestre 2012</bibRefCitation>
: 259, 261 (plate); 
<bibRefCitation id="BBA112DAA7A8B70366420B1905FC7538" author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="386 - 390" refId="B269" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora D'Italia. Edagricole, Bologna: 386 - 390" title="Flora D'Italia" year="1982">Pignatti 1982</bibRefCitation>
: 388; 
<bibRefCitation id="6A23EE4B6364F417CBDC3EAFE4D30D90" author="Tohme, G" journalOrPublisher="National Council for Scientific Research, Beirut" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 609" refId="B363" refString="Tohme, G, Tohme, H, 2007. Illustrated Flora of Lebanon. National Council for Scientific Research, Beirut: 1 - 609" title="Illustrated Flora of Lebanon" year="2007">
<normalizedToken id="22DD127FA8A4E7A0906B8FF9BBC2DF63" originalValue="Tohmé">Tohme</normalizedToken>
