<subSubSection id="9BBC81DE29888C6A409889898F4F1979" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C3FF4A9355B8662EB0717AB48E752E8B" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B53D103DB906B92859E96298122F35F5" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
We recognise two subspecies, which intergrade occasionally (e.g. 
<emphasis id="3258B10BF8E6B186A51D8FC0EDA1415D" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Ascherson</emphasis>
1054 from the Libyan desert in Egypt, 
<emphasis id="098B66CAA500F7863E528F40433D3BAC" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Finlay</emphasis>
s.n. from Madeira).
</paragraph>
